Last year I tweeted about something I called cozy futurism;
Cool-shit futurism (space colonization, moon telescopes, tech for the sake of tech to some extent) vs cozy futurism (urban reform, renewable energy, solving climate change; focusing on specific problems and having tech as an ends) are categories I&#39;ve been thinking about recently
&mdash; José Luis Ricón Fernández de la Puente (@ArtirKel) November 10, 2020

